  "title": "1D kinematics-acceleration with no change in speed",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A cart is moving along a straight track and has velocity <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 0.5 meter per second\"><math alttext=\"positive 0.5 meter per second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mn>0.5</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m/s</mtext></math></span></span> and positive acceleration at time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 second\"><math alttext=\"1 second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>. At time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 seconds\"><math alttext=\"3 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>, the cart reaches a maximum speed. At time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 seconds\"><math alttext=\"4 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>, the cart again has velocity <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 0.5 meters per second\"><math alttext=\"positive 0.5 meters per second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mn>0.5</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m/s</mtext></math></span></span>, but with negative acceleration. A student claims that the average acceleration of the cart between time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 second\"><math alttext=\"1 second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 seconds\"><math alttext=\"4 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span> time is zero. Is the studentâ€™s claim correct? Why or why not?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Yes, because the final velocity of the cart is equal to the initial velocity.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Yes, because the cart returns to its original position.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">No, because the values of the acceleration at time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 second\"><math alttext=\"1 second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span> and time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 seconds\"><math alttext=\"4 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span> are unknown.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">No, because the cart spends more time with a positive acceleration than with a negative acceleration.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
